The paper deals with a problem of sensor placement and coverage in the plane, which is a classic problem in computational geometry (cs.CG). The problem involves optimization and approximation algorithms, which are also relevant to the sub-categories of data structures (cs.DS), discrete mathematics (cs.DM), and machine learning (cs.LG). The use of linear programming and maximal matching techniques suggests the sub-category of social and information networks (cs.SI) as well.
